    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required level. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level of 3 due to single-configuration testing; this gap is accepted given regulatory precedent for ASTM F1717 as the primary benchmark for pedicle screw constructs and the medium model risk level. All three primary QoIs satisfy the quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for supporting the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw.",
